In this article, President Trump speaks at a meeting with mayors, sheriffs, and local leaders from California who are opposed to the state's sanctuary laws. He criticizes California's laws that provide sanctuary to illegal immigrants, arguing that they release dangerous criminals into communities. He praises the efforts of those in attendance who have resisted these laws and highlights the work of Attorney General Jeff Sessions, Homeland Security Secretary Kirstjen Nielsen, and Deputy ICE Director Tom Homan. Trump also discusses the progress of the border wall and the need for comprehensive immigration reform. Various attendees share their experiences and concerns about crime and illegal immigration in their communities. They express their support for stronger border security and the repeal of sanctuary state laws. Overall, the article highlights Trump's commitment to cracking down on illegal immigration and the support he receives from local leaders who share his views.